(161, 1368516100, 'ClickTracker', 'ClickTracker: Keep track of your clicking patterns (for instance, how much you switch tabs, and go back to check your email), and compares them on productive vs. nonproductive days. Thereâ€™s a study that shows people who are depressed and in front of a computer tend to switch tabs a lot. My guess is that if you log someoneâ€™s click patterns and show them how much time they are wasting, they will shape up rather fast! #self-quantification ~holden1@mit.edu ', 0, NULL, '', 0, 187, 14, 1, '161'),
